A4.text: the fortress settlement of Clausentum was established

A5.text: Dubris, also known as Portus Dubris and Dubrae, was a port in Roman Britain on the site of present-day Dover, Kent, England.

A6.text: At its peak, Dubris was a major trading centre, taking over from Rutupiae as the main Roman cross-Channel port.
